BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Ragtime
DTSTART:20260719T000000Z
DTEND:20260719T025000Z
DTSTAMP:20260326T190233Z
UID:998676
DESCRIPTION:<p>It was the music of something beginning&hellip\;<br /><br /
 ><em>Ragtime</em> is a sweeping musical adaption of E.L. Doctorow&rsquo\;s
  novel that follows three fictional families in pursuit of the American Dr
 eam at the dawn of the 20th Century: Black pianist Coalhouse Walker\, Jr. 
 and his beloved Sarah\, Jewish immigrant Tateh and his little girl\, and a
  wealthy white family led by matriarch Mother. All grasping for the same d
 ream\, if only they can hold on to it.<br /><br />Featuring a lush score b
 y Stephen Flaherty and Lynn Ahrens\, a stirring book by Terrence McNally a
 nd original orchestrations by William David Brohn\, all of whom won Tony A
 wards for their work\, RAGTIME weaves fictional narratives with real histo
 rical figures and events\, creating a rich tapestry that blurs the line be
 tween personal struggle and national identity\, making history feel both i
 ntimate and epic.<br /><br />LCT Kewsong Lee Artistic Director Lear deBess
 onet (Tony-nominated for her celebrated 2022 revival of <em>Into the Woods
 </em>) directs a new production\, envisioned for the grand Vivian Beaumont
  stage\, starring Tony nominee Joshua Henry (<em>Into the Woods</em>\, <em
 >Carousel</em>)\, Olivier and Grammy nominee Caissie Levy (<em>Hair</em>\,
  <em>Frozen</em>)\, and Tony winner Brandon Uranowitz (<em>Leopoldstadt</e
 m>\, LCT's <em>Falsettos</em>).</p>
LOCATION:Lincoln Center Theater-Vivian Beaumont\, 150 West 65th Street\, N
 ew York NY 10023
END:VEVENT
